1. To compile the program "My_Alarm.c", use the following command:

      cc -o My_Alarm My_Alarm.c -D_POSIX_PTHREAD_SEMANTICS -lpthread 
   
   or by using the "make" command or just running the "Makefile"

2. Type "My_Alarm" to run the executable code.

3. At the prompt "alarm>", type in the number of seconds at which
   the alarm should expire, followed by the text of the message.
   For example:

   alarm> 2 Good Morning!

4. To exit from the program, type Ctrl-d.
